  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: The Sign Of Virtue Complete
---
\"Among level things, water at rest is the most perfect, and therefore
it can serve as a standard. It guards what is inside and shows no
movement outside. Virtue is the establishment of perfect harmony.
Though virtue takes no form, things cannot break away from it."
